16/10/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Sarajevo Canton Court Trial Panel sentenced retired Bosnian Serb policeman Borislav Berjan to seven years in prison Monday (October 15th) for war crimes committed in the Ilidza municipality from 1992 to 1993. 
The court found that Berjan personally helped arm Serbs in the area and voluntarily participated in banishment, torture and illegal arrests. 
He also ordered the killings of civilians and war prisoners there and robbed Croatian civilians of property. 
(RTRS, Fena, NTV Hayat - 15/10/07)
